COMPONENT NAME: CKM Teradata COMPONENT VERSION: 10.1.3.3 AUTHOR: Oracle COMPATIBILITY: ODI 10.1.3.5.0 and above
DESCRIPTION This module controls the validity of the constraints of a Datastore and rejects the invalid records in an error table. It can be used for static controls as well as flow controls.
OPTIONS - DROP_ERROR_TABLE: Drop error table before validation? - DROP_CHECK_TABLE: Drop error summary table before validation? - PRIMARY_INDEX: Primary index for error/check table - COLLECT_STATS: Gather statistics on error table after validation?
LIMITATIONS - Can only be used if the target table/ controlled table has a primary key or an unique key. - Data cleansing can be performed only if a primary key is defined on the controlled table.

When this option is set to YES, the error table will be dropped each time a control is performed on the target table. This means that any rejected records, identified and stored during previous control operations, will be lost.

When this option is set to YES, the check table (SNP_CHECK_TAB, created in the default physical schema of the physical server that hosts the controlled table) will be dropped each time a control is performed on the table. This table contains a summary of the erroneous data found in any datastores hosted on the same physical data server (regardless of their physical schemas)

Specify primary index for error/check table. Teradata uses the PI to spread data accross AMPs. It is important that the chosen PI has a high cardinality (many distint values) to ensure evenly spread data to allow maximum processing performance. Pleaes follow Teradata's recommandation on choosing a primary index, e.g. Teradata Database Design, Chapter "Primary Indexes" When CKM is used inside an interface, best performance is achieved by matching this option with PRIMARY_INDEX option of IKM. Valid options are [PK] Primary key of error/check table [UK] Update key set in interface, only allowed for flow control [SCD_NK] Natural key of table <list of cols> This comma separated list of target columns defines the primary index. If no value is set (empty), no index will be created. NB: Teradata will automatically choose the first column of the table for the PI. [NOPI] Do not specify primary index for error/check table (Teradata 13.0 & above only).
Collect statistics on primary index of error table?

insert into <%=odiRef.getTable("L","ERR_NAME", "W")%> ( ERR_TYPE, ERR_MESS, CHECK_DATE, ORIGIN, CONS_NAME, CONS_TYPE, <%=odiRef.getColList("", "[COL_NAME]", ",\n\t", "", "MAP")%> ) select '<%=odiRef.getInfo("CT_ERR_TYPE")%>', '<%=odiRef.getCK("MESS")%>', <%=odiRef.getInfo("DEST_DATE_FCT")%>, '<%=odiRef.getInfo("CT_ORIGIN")%>', '<%=odiRef.getCK("COND_NAME")%>', 'CK', <%=odiRef.getColList("", "[COL_NAME]", ",\n\t", "", "MAP")%> from <%=odiRef.getTable("L", "CT_NAME", "A")%> <%=odiRef.getInfo("DEST_TAB_ALIAS_WORD")%> <%=odiRef.getCK("COND_ALIAS")%> where not (<%=odiRef.getCK("COND_SQL")%>) <%=odiRef.getFilter()%>

insert into <%=odiRef.getTable("L","ERR_NAME", "W")%> ( ERR_TYPE, ERR_MESS, CHECK_DATE, ORIGIN, CONS_NAME, CONS_TYPE, <%=odiRef.getColList("", "[COL_NAME]", ",\n\t", "", "MAP")%> ) select '<%=odiRef.getInfo("CT_ERR_TYPE")%>', '<%=odiRef.getNotNullCol("MESS")%>', <%=odiRef.getInfo("DEST_DATE_FCT")%>, '<%=odiRef.getInfo("CT_ORIGIN")%>', '<%=odiRef.getNotNullCol("COL_NAME")%>', 'NN', <%=odiRef.getColList("", "[COL_NAME]", ",\n\t", "", "MAP")%> from <%=odiRef.getTable("L", "CT_NAME", "A")%> where <%=odiRef.getNotNullCol("COL_NAME")%> is null <%=odiRef.getFilter()%>
Collect stats on PI of error table

<% if (odiRef.getOption("COLLECT_STATS").equals("1") &&
    odiRef.getOption("PRIMARY_INDEX").length() > 0 && 
    !odiRef.getOption("PRIMARY_INDEX").equals("[NOPI]")) { %>
collect stats using sample on  <%=odiRef.getTable("L", "ERR_NAME", "W")%> <% 
      /* update key used for PI ? */
      if (odiRef.getOption("PRIMARY_INDEX").equals("[UK]")) 
          out.print( odiRef.getColList("column (", "[COL_NAME]", ",", ")", "UK") );
      /* primary key used for PI ? */
      else if (odiRef.getOption("PRIMARY_INDEX").equals("[PK]")) 
          out.print( odiRef.getColList("column (", "[COL_NAME]", ",", ")", "PK") );
      /* natural key used for PI ? */
      else if (odiRef.getOption("PRIMARY_INDEX").equals("[SCD_NK]")) 
          out.print( odiRef.getColList("column (", "[COL_NAME]", ",", ")", "SCD_NK") );
      /* column list used for PI ? */
      else if (odiRef.getOption("PRIMARY_INDEX").length() > 0) 
          out.print( "column (" + odiRef.getOption("PRIMARY_INDEX") + ")" );
	} else { %>
-- No stats, as no PRIMARY_INDEX specified.
<%};%>

/* Stats for error recycling */ <% if ( odiRef.getOption("COLLECT_STATS").equals("1") && odiRef.getOption("PRIMARY_INDEX").length() > 0 && !odiRef.getOption("PRIMARY_INDEX").equals("[NOPI]") ) { %> collect stats using sample on <%=odiRef.getTable("L","ERR_NAME", "W")%> column (ERR_TYPE,ORIGIN ) <% } else { %> -- No stats, as no PRIMARY_INDEX specified or COLLECT_STATS disabled. <%};%>

Insert check sum into check table

insert into <%=odiRef.getTable("L","CHECK_NAME", "W")%> ( CATALOG_NAME, SCHEMA_NAME, RESOURCE_NAME, FULL_RES_NAME, ERR_TYPE, ERR_MESS, CHECK_DATE, ORIGIN, CONS_NAME, CONS_TYPE, ERR_COUNT ) select '<%=odiRef.getTargetTable("CATALOG")%>', '<%=odiRef.getTargetTable("SCHEMA")%>', '<%=odiRef.getTargetTable("TABLE_NAME")%>', '<%=odiRef.getTable("L","TARG_NAME","D")%>', E.ERR_TYPE, E.ERR_MESS, E.CHECK_DATE, E.ORIGIN, E.CONS_NAME, E.CONS_TYPE, count(*) from <%=odiRef.getTable("L","ERR_NAME", "W")%> E where E.ERR_TYPE = '<%=odiRef.getInfo("CT_ERR_TYPE")%>' and E.ORIGIN = '<%=odiRef.getInfo("CT_ORIGIN")%>' group by E.ERR_TYPE, E.ERR_MESS, E.CHECK_DATE, E.ORIGIN, E.CONS_NAME, E.CONS_TYPE

create table <%=odiRef.getTable("L","CHECK_NAME","W")%>, no fallback, no before journal, no after journal ( CATALOG_NAME <%=odiRef.getDataType("DEST_VARCHAR", "100", "")%> <%=odiRef.getInfo("DEST_DDL_NULL")%> , SCHEMA_NAME <%=odiRef.getDataType("DEST_VARCHAR", "100", "")%> <%=odiRef.getInfo("DEST_DDL_NULL")%> , RESOURCE_NAME <%=odiRef.getDataType("DEST_VARCHAR", "100", "")%> <%=odiRef.getInfo("DEST_DDL_NULL")%>, FULL_RES_NAME <%=odiRef.getDataType("DEST_VARCHAR", "100", "")%> <%=odiRef.getInfo("DEST_DDL_NULL")%>, ERR_TYPE <%=odiRef.getDataType("DEST_VARCHAR", "1", "")%> <%=odiRef.getInfo("DEST_DDL_NULL")%>, ERR_MESS <%=odiRef.getDataType("DEST_VARCHAR", "250", "")%> <%=odiRef.getInfo("DEST_DDL_NULL")%> , CHECK_DATE <%=odiRef.getDataType("DEST_DATE", "", "")%> <%=odiRef.getInfo("DEST_DDL_NULL")%>, ORIGIN <%=odiRef.getDataType("DEST_VARCHAR", "100", "")%> <%=odiRef.getInfo("DEST_DDL_NULL")%>, CONS_NAME <%=odiRef.getDataType("DEST_VARCHAR", "35", "")%> <%=odiRef.getInfo("DEST_DDL_NULL")%>, CONS_TYPE <%=odiRef.getDataType("DEST_VARCHAR", "2", "")%> <%=odiRef.getInfo("DEST_DDL_NULL")%>, ERR_COUNT <%=odiRef.getDataType("DEST_NUMERIC", "10", "")%> <%=odiRef.getInfo("DEST_DDL_NULL")%> ) <% /* No PI ? */ if (odiRef.getOption("PRIMARY_INDEX").equals("[NOPI]")) out.print( " no primary index " ); else out.print( " primary index (FULL_RES_NAME, ERR_TYPE , CONS_NAME, CONS_TYPE)" ); %>

delete from <%=odiRef.getTable("L","CHECK_NAME", "W")%> where CATALOG_NAME = '<%=odiRef.getTargetTable("CATALOG")%>' and SCHEMA_NAME = '<%=odiRef.getTargetTable("SCHEMA")%>' and ORIGIN = '<%=odiRef.getInfo("CT_ORIGIN")%>' and ERR_TYPE = '<%=odiRef.getInfo("CT_ERR_TYPE")%>'
delete from <%=odiRef.getTable("L","ERR_NAME", "W")%> where ERR_TYPE = '<%=odiRef.getInfo("CT_ERR_TYPE")%>' and ORIGIN = '<%=odiRef.getInfo("CT_ORIGIN")%>'
